<report type:"WARNING">
  description : "VCSA-70-000060 - The vCenter Server must require multifactor authentication."
  info        : "Without the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged functions is greatly increased.

Multifactor authentication requires using two or more factors to achieve authentication.

Factors include:
(i) something a user knows (e.g., password/PIN);
(ii) something a user has (e.g., cryptographic identification device, token); or
(iii) something a user is (e.g., biometric).

Satisfies: SRG-APP-000149, SRG-APP-000080, SRG-APP-000150, SRG-APP-000391, SRG-APP-000402

NOTE: Nessus has not performed this check. Please review the benchmark to ensure target compliance."
