<report type:"WARNING">
  description : "VCSA-70-000268 - The vCenter Server must set the distributed port group Forged Transmits policy to 'Reject'."
  info        : "If the virtual machine operating system changes the Media Access Control (MAC) address, the operating system can send frames with an impersonated source MAC address at any time. This allows an operating system to stage malicious attacks on the devices in a network by impersonating a network adaptor authorized by the receiving network.

