<report type:"WARNING">
  description : "VCSA-70-000273 - The vCenter Server must not configure VLAN Trunking unless Virtual Guest Tagging (VGT) is required and authorized."
  info        : "When a port group is set to VLAN Trunking, the vSwitch passes all network frames in the specified range to the attached virtual machines without modifying the virtual local area network (VLAN) tags. In vSphere, this is referred to as VGT.

