<report type:"WARNING">
  description : "VCSA-70-000284 - The vCenter Server must restrict access to the default roles with cryptographic permissions."
  info        : "In vSphere, a number of default roles contain permission to perform cryptographic operations such as Key Management Server (KMS) functions and encrypting and decrypting virtual machine disks. These roles must be reserved for cryptographic administrators where virtual machine encryption and/or vSAN encryption is in use.

